post_text: All CCSS schools and offices will be open Wednesday, August 26th, 2020. Pre-K thru Grade 6 will report to their campuses. Grades 7 - 12 will follow their regular schedule for virtual instruction. We will continue to monitor the path of Hurricane Laura and will make a decision about future closing(s) tomorrow.
text: All CCSS schools and offices will be open Wednesday, August 26th, 2020. Pre-K thru Grade 6 will report to their campuses. Grades 7 - 12 will follow their regular schedule for virtual instruction. We will continue to monitor the path of Hurricane Laura and will make a decision about future closing(s) tomorrow.

post_text:
Due to the predicted impact of Hurricane Marco, all Central Community School System offices and schools will be closed Monday, August 24th, and Tuesday, August 25th. These closures include instruction that is delivered in person and online. All school and district activities are canceled. District personnel will be working with local emergency agencies to continue monitoring the path of Marco as well as the predicted path of Tropical Storm Laura. A decision for additional school closures will be made after monitoring the path of TS Laura on Monday and Tuesday.

Please remember to check our website www.centralcss.org for official decisions regarding school closures.

post_text: Due to Governor Edwards’ executive order, all schools and the district office in the Central Community School System will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th until Monday, April 13th. During this time, ALL school-related functions have been canceled. We’ve been preparing for this eventuality for a number of days. We have a strong plan in place and will share those details early next week, along with answering questions around the school calendar and other items. Please continue to check our website (centralcss.org/covid19) for updates and information during this time.

Central Community School System is introducing a new way for parents to pay for field trips, yearbooks, spirit wear, athletic fees, and more. It’s called School Cash Online.
School Cash Online is a web-based program that integrates online payment options with school level accounting.

Click here to watch an instructional video about the program:
https://kevgroup.com/intro-to-school-cash-online/

Click here to access the program:
https://centralcss.schoolcashonline.com/

Please contact your child's school if you have questions about the program.

*Note: All online purchases include a small transaction fee.

post_text:
Announcing New Central Middle School Parent Resources
1. CMS “App”
2. Eureka Math Parent Resources

How to Install the New CMS “App” on Your Phone

iOS – Safari: enter goo.gl/vwi8M6 , select the share box, and select “Add to Home Screen,” name it “CMS.”
-------------------------------------------------
Android – Chrome: enter goo.gl/vwi8M6, click the three dots, and select “Add to Home Screen,” name it “CMS.”
-------------------------------------------------
This “app” will direct you to the information you are searching for on the CMS website. Use your browser’s back button to return to the “app” from the Internet. Contact your school if you need assistance to join the Student Progress Center.

Where to Find Eureka Math Help:
1. Go to the CMS or CCSS website (centralcss.org)
2. Click the PARENTS tab at the top of the page
3. Click MATH HELP
4. Click your child’s grade level
---Or---
Click the Math Help icon on the CMS “App”
